Your project uses **MSTest v2 (2.2.10)** on `net6.0`. Here are the breaking changes that apply to your code:

---

### 1. `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` overload removed
Lines 13 & 20 — v3 removes the untyped `(object, object)` overloads. You'll get compile errors.

```csharp
// Before (v2)
Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual);
Assert.AreSame(obj, obj);

// After (v3)
Assert.AreEqual<object>(expected, actual);
Assert.AreSame<object>(obj, obj);
```

### 2. `DataRow` strict type matching
Lines 24–25 — `1L`/`2L` are `long`, but the parameter `id` is `int`. v2 allowed implicit conversion; v3 does not.

```csharp
// Before (v2)
[DataRow(1L, "Alice")]
public void GetUserName_ReturnsCorrectName(int id, string expectedName)

// After (v3) — pick one:
[DataRow(1, "Alice")]      // change literal to int
// OR
public void GetUserName_ReturnsCorrectName(long id, string expectedName)  // change param to long
```

### 3. `[Timeout]` behavior unified
Line 32 — v3 unifies timeout behavior across .NET Core and Framework. Your `[Timeout(3000)]` will still compile but may behave differently. Verify after upgrading.

